URL: https://www.lintcode.com/problem/partition-array/description

Description
Given an array nums of integers and an int k, partition the array (i.e move the elements in "nums") such that:

All elements < k are moved to the left
All elements >= k are moved to the right
Return the partitioning index, i.e the first index i nums[i] >= k.
You should do really partition in array nums instead of just counting the numbers of integers smaller than k.
If all elements in nums are smaller than k, then return nums.length
Have you met this question in a real interview?  Yes
Example
If nums = [3,2,2,1] and k=2, a valid answer is 1.
Challenge
Can you partition the array in-place and in O(n)?


Answer: 
1: Use two pointer to partition it.
2: Time Complexity: O(n)
3: A little bit different from the partition part in quick sort


public class Solution {
    /**
     * @param nums: The integer array you should partition
     * @param k: An integer
     * @return: The index after partition
     */
    public int partitionArray(int[] nums, int k) {
        // write your code here
        if (nums == null || nums.length == 0) {
            return 0;
        } 
        int l = 0;
        int r = nums.length - 1;
        while(l < r){
            while(l < nums.length && nums[l] < k){
                l++;
            }
            while(r > 0 && nums[r] >= k){
                r--;
            }
            if(l < r){
                int temp = nums[l];
                nums[l] = nums[r];
                nums[r] = temp;
                l++;
                r--;
            }
        }
        if(l == nums.length - 1){
            return nums.length;
        }
        else{
            return l; // can not return right! for array[r] may be smaller than pivot!
        }
    }
}
